t;:20,&quot;y&quot;:20,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:23,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1625}\">Calcium Carbonate Pharma Grade</h2>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:59,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:62,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1664}\">At MLA we are proud of the pace with which we have made our company leading calcium carbonate pharma-grade manufacturers in India, providing R&amp;D and one-stop production services. Intensifying our success is our commitment to persistent optimization and investing in the upcoming future. Our mission is to accelerate and enlarge our practice of launching new drugs, APIs, formulations, and clinical research services. By improving our capabilities, and constantly maintaining our verve, we have built a knowledge base that we are ready to share with the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:134,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:62,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1739}\">The product is manufactured in a Drug Controller authorized India FDA approved facility located at Kanpur. We have AHU with hepa filters for a controlled and sterilized manufacturing environment. We also have an in-house microbiology lab. We are also audited and certified with state GMP, which few manufacturers in our line are. We manufacture products conforming to IP/ BP/USP/ JP / EP/ NF monographs. The site master file is available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:210,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:20,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1815}\">We also have products in DC form ( granular ) used for tableting. Normally the binder used is Starch or Maltodextrin as per the buyer&#39;s preference, around 5 %.</p>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:244,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:41,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1849}\">We supply calcium carbonate pharma-grade that is used for a number of medical preparations like nutritional calcium supplements and antacid tablets. The highly purified forms of calcium carbonate are used in edible products, beverages, and pharmaceutical companies and markets.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:300,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:18,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1905}\">The Product - Calcium Carbonate Pharma Grade</h2>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:334,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:62,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:1939}\">Calcium carbonate is an inactive chemical compound that is extracted from mineral rock foundations such as marble, limestone, etc. It is commonly found in rocks and is the main constituent of shells of marine animals, pearls, snails, and eggs. It is formed when calcium ions in hard water react with carbonate ions to create limescale. For medicinal purposes, it is used as a calcium supplement or as an antacid, but over-consumption could be harmful and lead to poor digestion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:409,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:20,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2014}\">It is also manufactured synthetically by passing carbon dioxide through hydrated lime to give a comparatively lighter product with lower bulk density.</p>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:443,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:62,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2048}\">They are required to be stored in well-closed containers. We, being the leading calcium carbonate pharma-grade exporters in India, hold a complete command of proper inspection and testing, with an inspection laboratory for raw materials and finished products with a guarantee of a 100% pass rate of the shipped products. The testing is organized in a three-tier process- first through the shopfloor lab, second through the factory quality, and then, at last, the central quality control.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:522,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:23,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2127}\">Classifications of Calcium Carbonate</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:561,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:18,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2166}\">Calcium carbonate is classified into three polymorphic forms:-</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:597,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:15,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2202}\"><strong bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:597,&quot;w&quot;:46,&quot;h&quot;:14,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2202}\">Calcite:</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:630,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:20,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2235}\">It is most stable and least soluble in nature. It is broadly found in metamorphic, sedimentary, and igneous rocks. Calcite is a common component of sedimentary rocks like limestone and marble.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:668,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:15,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2273}\"><strong bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:668,&quot;w&quot;:65,&quot;h&quot;:14,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2273}\">Aragonite:</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:701,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:41,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2306}\">It is less stable and more soluble in comparison to calcite. Biological and physical procedures like precipitation by freshwater and marine helps in the formation of aragonite. It is generally used for removing the pollutants like cobalt, zinc, and lead from polluted wastewaters.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:760,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:15,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2365}\"><strong bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:760,&quot;w&quot;:51,&quot;h&quot;:14,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2365}\">Vaterite:</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:792,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:41,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2397}\">Vaterite is usually hexagonal in shape and is less stable than both the minerals calcite as well as aragonite but solubility is higher. It is majorly used in regenerative medicine and in personal care products.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:850,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:23,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2455}\">General Properties of Calcium Carbonate</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:890,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:18,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2495}\">Physical Properties</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:923,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:83,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2528}\">\r\n	<li bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:60,&quot;y&quot;:923,&quot;w&quot;:1047,&quot;h&quot;:20,&quot;abs_x&quot;:346,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2528}\">The pure form of calcium carbonate is an odorless powder.</li>\r\n	<li bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:60,&quot;y&quot;:944,&quot;w&quot;:1047,&quot;h&quot;:20,&quot;abs_x&quot;:346,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2549}\">Color is super white</li>\r\n	<li bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:60,&quot;y&quot;:965,&quot;w&quot;:1047,&quot;h&quot;:20,&quot;abs_x&quot;:346,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2570}\">Density is 2.71 g/mL and melting point is 1,339 &deg;C in calcite form</li>\r\n	<li bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:60,&quot;y&quot;:986,&quot;w&quot;:1047,&quot;h&quot;:20,&quot;abs_x&quot;:346,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2591}\">Aragonite has a density of 2.83 g/mL and a melting point of 825 &deg;C.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1022,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:18,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2627}\">Chemical Properties</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1055,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:62,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2660}\">\r\n	<li bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:60,&quot;y&quot;:1055,&quot;w&quot;:1047,&quot;h&quot;:20,&quot;abs_x&quot;:346,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2660}\">Insoluble in water</li>\r\n	<li bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:60,&quot;y&quot;:1076,&quot;w&quot;:1047,&quot;h&quot;:20,&quot;abs_x&quot;:346,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2681}\">Stable at normal temperature</li>\r\n	<li bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:60,&quot;y&quot;:1097,&quot;w&quot;:1047,&quot;h&quot;:20,&quot;abs_x&quot;:346,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2702}\">At very high temperatures, when calcium carbonate is heated, it decomposes to form calcium oxide, releasing carbon dioxide.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1134,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:23,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2739}\"><meta charset=\"utf-8\" /><b bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1134,&quot;w&quot;:724,&quot;h&quot;:21,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2739}\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-88ae4adb-7fff-dda5-f935-24cbcb698c61\">Why choose us as your Calcium Carbonate Pharma Grade Suppliers in India?&nbsp;</b></h2>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1173,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:62,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2778}\">With our solid and distinct infrastructure, <a bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:254,&quot;y&quot;:1176,&quot;w&quot;:65,&quot;h&quot;:14,&quot;abs_x&quot;:540,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2781}\" href=\"https://www.mlagroup.com/\">MLA Group</a> is&nbsp;the leading calcium carbonate pharma-grade manufacturers in the world. We are one of the very few calcium carbonate pharma-grade suppliers that incorporate only superior quality raw materials and with manufacturing consistency. We are renowned chemical manufacturers with a track record of safety and sustainability, accumulated by our dedication and service towards humanity, allegiance to innovation and federation, and uncompromising cohesion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1249,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:83,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2854}\">Our engineers are specialized in the area they provide service and are persistently working to find new and better ways to enhance their expertise. We provide the mandatory resources for the proper handling of our chemical products through color-coded labels, wall cards, tech sheets, safety data sheets, and color-coded container tags. For the calcium carbonate pharma-grade manufacturing range, we ensure that all labels and tech sheets are easy to read so that employees could easily, quickly, and precisely identify any hazards involved while working with a specific chemical.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1348,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:23,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2953}\">FAQs</h2>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1388,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:20,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2993}\"><strong bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1391,&quot;w&quot;:521,&quot;h&quot;:14,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:2996}\">What precautions need to be taken while storing Calcium Carbonate Pharma Grade?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1421,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:41,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:3026}\">Store calcium carbonate Pharma Grade in a dry place. The recommended temperature for storage should lie between 15 &deg;C to 25 &deg;C. Use general ventilation. Keep it away from food, beverages, and animal foods.</p>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1476,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:20,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:3081}\"><strong bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1479,&quot;w&quot;:609,&quot;h&quot;:14,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:3084}\">Why should I choose MLA Group of industries as my Calcium Carbonate Pharma Grade suppliers?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1510,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:41,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:3115}\">MLA Group of industries is globally known for meeting the industry standards at all times when it comes to the quality of material, which has established us as one of the leading calcium carbonate pharma-grade exporters in the world. Keeping in mind our customer&#39;s needs and convenience, we ensure strict quality controls and fair market prices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1564,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:20,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:3169}\"><strong bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1568,&quot;w&quot;:436,&quot;h&quot;:14,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:3173}\">Can Calcium Carbonate Pharma Grade turn into a dangerous product?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p bis_size=\"{&quot;x&quot;:20,&quot;y&quot;:1598,&quot;w&quot;:1127,&quot;h&quot;:41,&quot;abs_x&quot;:306,&quot;abs_y&quot;:3203}\">Not really. Calcium carbonate pharma grade is not a dangerous product but can be harmful if consumed in large amounts. Common symptoms of calcium carbonate pharma-grade overdose can be abdominal pain, bone pain, depression, constipation, diarrhea, etc.</p>\r\n', '', '<h2>General Applications of Calcium Carbonate Pharma Grade</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>At the time of fermentation of antibiotics to buffer pH of broth, the precipitated form of calcium carbonate is added.</li>\r\n	<li>For the preparation of calcium salt, making of nutritional supplements, and for food fortification like ascorbate, calcium citrate, etc. highly purified calcium is used as the raw materials.</li>\r\n	<li>In the manufacturing process of buffered aspirins</li>\r\n	<li>As excipients for tablets</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '2024-04-29 06:32:56', '2025-10-24 11:52:02'),
(75, 'Zinc Oxide ', 'zinc-oxide', 'Leading Zinc Oxide Active manufacturer & supplier in India', 'As one of the leading manufacturer and exporter of Zinc Oxide Active in the world, we supply high quality product processed in certified plant in best price.', 'test', 'product-image/zinc-oxide.webp', '\"60,61,62,63\"', '', 'Unpublished', '<h3>ROLE OF ZINC OXIDE (ACTIVATED / TRANSPARENT)</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>MLA Group of Industries is a global exporter of chemical products specialized in the manufacturing of chemical products. We are also known as leading Zinc Oxide Manufacturers in India. We are known to be a supplier of Zinc Oxide at very competitive prices. Organic accelerators used in rubber compounding are almost always dependant on the presence of activators. Zinc Oxide is the most important of such activators.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>ZINCOSIL NK-A AND NK-T</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Because of their very small particle sizes zinc-oxide active &amp; transparent (NK-A &amp; NK-T) cause very powerful activation of the cure. Depending on the type and amount of accelerator present they can considerably delay the onset of cure without simultaneously extending the total curing time.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Because of stronger activating effect, the amount of this substance needed for the same modulus is lesser as compared to ordinary Zinc Oxide.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Unlike ordinary Zinc-Oxide, ZINCOSIL NK-T is compatible with the production of transparent goods as it does not impair the transparency of the vulcanizates when added in small and moderately large amounts.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;They cause no changes in the colour of the vulcanizates. They reduce yellowing in white and light coloured goods which are exposed to strong light.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;As they do not have pigmenting properties, they do not influence effect of colour pigments provided they are not too heavily loaded.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Due to exceptionally low lead compound contents they are particularly suitable for vulcanizates intended to be practically free from heavy metals.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;They do not boom.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>APPLICATIONS</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Can be used as activators in : 1. sulphur cures 2. peroxide cures (often) 3. sulphurless metallic-oxide cures. Used as crosslinking agent for lattices with reactive groups and for CR.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Suitable for following types of rubber-NR, IR, BR, SBR, NBR, IIR, CR, EPDM, CSM.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Transparent goods i.e. injection caps, condoms, gloves, lab. appartus.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Rubber foam.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Highly elastic vulcanizates (spring components).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>PACKING</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>(25 kgs) In new laminated H.D.P.E. bags with loose polythene liner inside.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>WHY USE ZINC OXIDE (ACTIVATED / TRANSPARENT)</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Our strong technical background in terms of R &amp; D facilities and scientific personnel has enabled us to optimize our production cost to provide you the best possible quality at a very reasonable price.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Equipped with a rubber laboratory, we have modified our product to give an excellent combination of various desirable properties in rubber.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Fineness of particles or surface area is the most important property which determines activity. We have optimised the surface area to give best results in rubber.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>ACTIVE ZINC OXIDE IS SUPERIOR TO CONVENTIONAL WHITE SEAL ZINC OXIDE( 99.5 % ) BECAUSE</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;White seal has a surface area only 5 sq mtr/gm whereas active has 40-50 sq mtr/gm, so its reactivity in rubber vulcanization complex formation is much better and it can be used in lower dosage upto 40 % in different grades.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Where as white seal can have lead and other heavy metals upto 2500 ppm, active zinc oxide has below 20 ppm. So there is no lead blackening, no microwave defects and no ageing deterioration in properties.</li>\r\n	<li>