inc-Oxide, ZINCOSIL NK-T is compatible with the production of transparent goods as it does not impair the transparency of the vulcanizates when added in small and moderately large amounts.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;They cause no changes in the colour of the vulcanizates. They reduce yellowing in white and light coloured goods which are exposed to strong light.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;As they do not have pigmenting properties, they do not influence effect of colour pigments provided they are not too heavily loaded.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Due to exceptionally low lead compound contents they are particularly suitable for vulcanizates intended to be practically free from heavy metals.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;They do not boom.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>APPLICATIONS</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Can be used as activators in : 1. sulphur cures 2. peroxide cures (often) 3. sulphurless metallic-oxide cures. Used as crosslinking agent for lattices with reactive groups and for CR.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Suitable for following types of rubber-NR, IR, BR, SBR, NBR, IIR, CR, EPDM, CSM.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Transparent goods i.e. injection caps, condoms, gloves, lab. appartus.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Rubber foam.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Highly elastic vulcanizates (spring components).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>PACKING</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>(25 kgs) In new laminated H.D.P.E. bags with loose polythene liner inside.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>WHY USE ZINC OXIDE (ACTIVATED / TRANSPARENT)</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Our strong technical background in terms of R &amp; D facilities and scientific personnel has enabled us to optimize our production cost to provide you the best possible quality at a very reasonable price.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Equipped with a rubber laboratory, we have modified our product to give an excellent combination of various desirable properties in rubber.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Fineness of particles or surface area is the most important property which determines activity. We have optimised the surface area to give best results in rubber.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>ACTIVE ZINC OXIDE IS SUPERIOR TO CONVENTIONAL WHITE SEAL ZINC OXIDE( 99.5 % ) BECAUSE</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;White seal has a surface area only 5 sq mtr/gm whereas active has 40-50 sq mtr/gm, so its reactivity in rubber vulcanization complex formation is much better and it can be used in lower dosage upto 40 % in different grades.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Where as white seal can have lead and other heavy metals upto 2500 ppm, active zinc oxide has below 20 ppm. So there is no lead blackening, no microwave defects and no ageing deterioration in properties.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Zincosil T -150 against Lanxess</strong>&nbsp;( Zno 93-95, surface area 40-50 sq mtr / gm ) : This grade can be used 30-40 % less dosage easily. An outside rubber lab report showing performance of our product vs Lanxess is enclosed.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Zincosil MLA -900 against white seal</strong>&nbsp;( Zno 90 %, surface area 15-25 sqmtr /gm ) : This grade can be used 10-30 % less than white seal.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Zincosil MLA -700 against white seal</strong>&nbsp;( Zinc complex 90-95 %, surface area 15-25 sqmtr /gm ) : This grade can be used 10-20 % less than white seal.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Zincosil MLA -200 against Pan Continental, Global thailand, AML Punjab etc</strong>&nbsp;( zinc complex 80-90 %, surface area 15-25 sq mtr/ gm ) : This grade gives much better properties than it&#39;s mentioned imported products and scorch safety is also much better.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '2024-04-29 06:36:20', '2024-12-04 08:18:36'),
(76, 'Sorbitan Tristearate', 'sorbitan-tristearate-manufacturers-in-india', 'Leading Sorbitan Tristearate Manufacturers in India', 'MLA Group is a leading manufacturer & supplier of Sorbitan Tristearate, we are one of the best exporters of STS in the world offering the best price.', '<script type=\"application/ld+json\">\r\n{\r\n  \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\r\n  \"@type\": \"FAQPage\",\r\n  \"mainEntity\": [{\r\n    \"@type\": \"Question\",\r\n    \"name\": \"What is the correct way to store Sorbitan Tristearate manufactured by you and what is the shelf life of the product?\",\r\n    \"acceptedAnswer\": {\r\n      \"@type\": \"Answer\",\r\n      \"text\": \"Sorbitan Tristearate is to be stored in the original packaging in a cool max.25-30°C & dry place, away from direct heat and sunlight.\r\nThe shelf life of Sorbitan Tristearate is one year from the date of production if stored under the aforementioned storage conditions and unopened packaging.\"\r\n    }\r\n  },{\r\n    \"@type\": \"Question\",\r\n    \"name\": \"What is the legal status of Sorbitan Tristearate manufactured by you?\",\r\n    \"acceptedAnswer\": {\r\n      \"@type\": \"Answer\",\r\n      \"text\": \"As leading Sorbitan Tristearate manufacturers in the world, our STS meets the specifications fixed by FAO/WHO and the EU. However, users must check for permissibility for the use of this product in foods in their own country as the food laws may differ in each country.\"\r\n    }\r\n  }]\r\n}\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Leading Sorbitan Tristearate Manufacturers in India\r\na\" />\r\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"MLA Group is a leading manufacturer & supplier of Sorbitan Tristearate, we are one of the best exporters of STS in the world offering the best price.\" />\r\n<meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://www.mlagroup.com/admin/codes/product-image/sorbitan-tri-stearate.webp\" />\r\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https://www.mlagroup.com/sorbitan-tristearate-manufacturers-in-india.html\" />\r\n<meta property=\"og:logo\" content=\"https://www.mlagroup.com/images/logo-MLA.png\" />\r\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"website\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<meta name=\"twitter:url\" content=\"https://www.mlagroup.com/sorbitan-tristearate-manufacturers-in-india.html\">\r\n<meta name=\"twitter:title\" content=\"Leading Sorbitan Tristearate Manufacturers in India\r\n\">\r\n<meta name=\"twitter:image\" content=\"https://www.mlagroup.com/admin/codes/product-image/sorbitan-tri-stearate.webp\">\r\n<meta name=\"twitter:description\" content=\"MLA Group is a leading manufacturer & supplier of Sorbitan Tristearate, we are one of the best exporters of STS in the world offering the best price.\" />\r\n<meta name=\"twitter:creator\" content=\"MLA Group\">\r\n\r\n', 'product-image/sorbitan-tri-stearate.webp', NULL, '', 'Unpublished', '<h2>Sorbitan Tristearate</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>MLA Group is a leading Sorbitan Tristearate manufacturer in India and is also a well-reputed global supplier of the product. Our rich expertise in this domain allows us to offer you premium quality Sorbitan Tristearate. The product is manufactured under the observation of our skilled industry professionals and is processed using only quality-raw materials and the latest methodology.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Sorbitan Tristearate - Product Description</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Sorbitan tristearate (abbr. STS) is a synthetic ester made by the reaction of sorbitol with stearic acid under controlled conditions with three molecules of stearic acid vs one molecule of sorbitol. It acts as a non-ionic surfactant. It can also be used as a dispersing agent in emulsifiers, stabilizers, and food, and in aerosol sprays. As a food additive, STS has the E number E492. Its main functions are to retard fat bloom in chocolates and prevent cloudy appearance in cooking oils.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Appearance: Creamish to Yellow Solid Waxy Flakes/ Beads</li>\r\n	<li>Acid Value: 15 max mgKOH/gm</li>\r\n	<li>Saponification Value: 176 &ndash; 188 mgKOH/gm</li>\r\n	<li>Hydroxyl Value: 66 - 80 mgKOH/gm</li>\r\n	<li>Lead (Pb): 2 max mg/kg</li>\r\n	<li>Melting Point: 55 - 85 &deg;C</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Why choose us as your Sorbitan Tristearate suppliers and exporters in India?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>MLA Group of Industries is an innovative and modern enterprise consisting of industry professionals with decades of research and development experience. Over the years, we have adhered to the philosophy of &quot;Perfection in quality. Perfection in services.&quot; Our three-tier quality control system ensures complete consistency in quality. Our in-house R&amp;D is committed to the development and application of new products solving specific processing issues. We are committed to ensuring food safety and contributing to the food industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to further meet international customers&#39; requirements for product quality, we have applied and obtained a series of certificates such as KOSHER, HALAL, etc.. to ensure the quality of our products, food safety, and meet customer needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>FAQs</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Answered by leading Sorbitan Tristearate exporters in India</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:null;\"><strong>What is the correct way to store Sorbitan Tristearate manufactured by you and what is the shelf life of the product?</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sorbitan Tristearate is to be stored in the original packaging in a cool max.25-30&deg;C &amp; dry place, away from direct heat and sunlight.<br />\r\nThe shelf life of Sorbitan Tristearate is one year from the date of production if stored under the aforementioned storage conditions and unopened packaging.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:null;\"><strong>What is the legal status of Sorbitan Tristearate manufactured by you?</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As leading Sorbitan Tristearate manufacturers in the world, our STS meets the specifications fixed by FAO/WHO and the EU. However, users must check for permissibility for the use of this product in foods in their own country as the food laws may differ in each country.</p>\r\n', '', '<h2>Uses of Sorbitan Tristearate</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A leading supplier and exporter of Sorbitan Tristearate (STS) in the world, we have been serving many food, pharmaceuticals, and cosmetic industries for several decades, providing them with an exceptional quality product at competitive prices.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Applications of Sorbitan Tristearate:</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4>Food Applications</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Used as surface-active substances, as emulsifiers that can be used to retard fat and anti-crystallizing agent in palm oil/cooking oils.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chocolates: Used as surface-active substances to reduce viscosity in chocolate formulations.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cocoa and chocolate products</li>\r\n	<li>Candies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Cooking oils: As an anti-crystallization agent in cooking oils</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bakery products</li>\r\n	<li>Toppings and coatings</li>\r\n	<li>Fat emulsions (e.g. spreads)</li>\r\n	<li>Beverage whiteners</li>\r\n	<li>Desserts</li>\r\n	<li>Jam, jellies, and marmalades</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Non-food applications</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cosmetics:</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>As a surfactant in cosmetics and personal care products. Skincare products, Makeup products, Moisturizers</li>\r\n	<li>Pharmaceuticals</li>\r\n	<li>Plastic food packaging</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '2024-04-29 06:41:58', '2025-06-09 13:24:07'),
(77, 'Sorbitol Monostearate', 'sorbitan-monosearate-manufacturers-in-india', 'Leading Sorbitol Monosearate Manufacturers in India', 'MLA Group is a leading manufacturer & supplier of Sorbitol Monosearate, we are one of the best exporters of SMS in the world offering the best price.', 'test', 'product-image/sorbitan-monostearate-500x500.webp', '', '', 'Unpublished', '<h2>Sorbitol Monostearate</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>MLA Group is a leading Sorbitan Monostearate manufacturers in India with over several decades of experience in the chemical industry. Our strong global chemical resource capabilities, professional control quality management system, and unparalleled customer support provide you with high-quality chemical products for industrial production. That&#39;s the reason MLA is a Star Export House with exports to over 50 countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our company follows a stringent 3-tier Quality Control System and FEMA ensuring the safety, consistency, and reliability of our product. Our reputation precedes us making us one of the most sought-after Sorbitan Monostearate manufacturers in the World.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Sorbitol Monostearate - Product Description</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Sorbitan monostearate is a synthetic ester made by the reaction of sorbitol with stearic acid under controlled conditions. It is used in the manufacture of food and healthcare products as a non-ionic surfactant with emulsifying, dispersing, and wetting properties. It is also employed to create synthetic fibers, metal machining fluid, and as a brightener in the leather industry. It is used in yeast manufacturing to protect the yeast from excess drying and also helps rehydrate the yeast cells.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sorbitan monostearate (abbreviation SMS), or Span 60, is an emulsifier esterified from sorbitol and stearic acid with the European food additive number E491. This ingredient is mostly used in baking yeast by improving the activity of instant dry yeast when the yeast is rehydrated before use.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Appearance and properties</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A white to yellow waxy bead or flake with a slight characteristic smell.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Hydrophilic-Lipophilic Balance (HLB)</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>With the HLB value of 4.7, meaning it is lipophilic and soluble in oil instead of water. It will form W/O (water-in-oil) type emulsion, and it is a strong emulsifying dispersion and has a wetting effect. A white to yellow waxy bead or flake with a slight characteristic smell.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Hydrophilic-Lipophilic Balance (HLB)</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>With the HLB value of 4.7, meaning it is lipophilic and soluble in oil instead of water. It will form W/O (water-in-oil) type emulsion, and it is a strong emulsifying dispersion and has a wetting effect</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Leading Sorbitan Monostearate suppliers in India</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Our Advantage</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4>100% genuine products</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We produce an authentic veg origin high-quality Sorbitan Monostearate. All types of compliances and quality assurance certifications are available.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Prompt responses</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We believe in fast and timely responses and are able to provide you with all the required information in a short period of time.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Competitive prices</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>While we provide high-quality Sorbitan Monostearate, we also make sure that we provide the best market prices for our products. This is made possible by our high economies of scale for various esters.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Excellent Customer Support</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We aim to provide the best sales and after-sales services to our customers, backed with technical and commercial support.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Fast and timely delivery</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We have an efficient logistics system in place to look over the delivery of products and also make sure of their safe transit.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>FAQs</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Answered by the leading Sorbitan Monostearate exporters in India</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Is the Sorbitan Monostearate manufactured by you Halal?</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, as the leading Sorbitan Monostearate manufacturers and exporters in the world, we provide a synthetic ester that would be halal complying with the Muslim policy as the fatty acid stearic acid is derived from vegetable oils instead of animal origins.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color:#000000\">Is Sorbitan Monostearate manufactured by you Vegan?</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, it is vegan as the raw material stearic acid is derived from vegetable oils and the manufacturing process is without the use of animal matter or products derived from animal origin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>What is the shelf life of Sorbitan Monostearate manufactured by you? Also, what is the legal status on the same?</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Shelf Life:</strong>&nbsp;Sorbitan Monostearate manufactured at MLA Group has a shelf life of one year from the date of production, if stored under mentioned storage conditions and unopened packaging.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Legal Status:</strong>Our SMS meets the specifications fixed by FAO/WHO and the EU. However, users must check for permissibility for the use of this product in foods in their own country as the food laws may differ in each country.</p>\r\n', '', '<h2>Uses of Sorbitan monostearate</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As leading suppliers and exporters of Sorbitan Monostearate in the world, we have been serving many foods and other industries with absolute consistency in quality at a reasonable cost.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Food Applications</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Sorbitan monostearate is used as an emulsifier, commonly together with polysorbates to keep water and oil mixed in many food products.<br />\r\nIt is commonly used in instant fat and oil emulsions, desserts, food supplements, cake, spread, margarine, coffee whiteners.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Dry yeast: maintain the moisture, increase the shelf life of dry yeast, and help the rehydration of yeast cells before blended with other dough ingredients.</li>\r\n	<li>Ice cream: promote emulsification of dairy fat, prevent the formation of ice crystals, and improve the mouthfeel.</li>\r\n	<li>Margarine: improve emulsion stability and reduce sandiness.</li>\r\n	<li>Whipping cream: improve foam volume and contribute to a nice and stiff foam.</li>\r\n	<li>Bread &amp; Cake: increase the loaf volume and improve the texture of bread and cake.</li>\r\n	<li>Confections and chocolate: stabilize the emulsion of oils and fats.</li>\r\n	<li>Flavored fermented milk products.</li>\r\n	<li>Beverage whiteners.</li>\r\n	<li>Fat and oil emulsions.</li>\r\n	<li>Sugar confectionery.</li>\r\n	<li>Chewing gum.</li>\r\n	<li>Decorations, coatings, and fillings.</li>\r\n	<li>Fine bakery wares.</li>\r\n	<li>Emulsified sauces.</li>\r\n	<li>Desserts.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Non-food applications</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pharmaceuticals &amp; Cosmetics</li>\r\n	<li>Plastic food wrap</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '2024-04-29 06:44:46', '2024-12-04 08:17:12');
